This paper is about using neural models to realize decision trees, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on ReLU networks that are piece-wise linear and locally constant, which are concepts that are commonly studied in the sub-fields of deep learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper applies the method to molecular property classification and regression tasks, which are problems that are often studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, and cs.DS.
